modules.description: This module provides access to the components of an HTTP request, including the body, target path, and headers. It operates on the `http_request` type, allowing retrieval of request data such as the request body as a string, the target URL path, and individual header values by name. Concrete use cases include extracting user input from request headers, reading API endpoints from the target path, and processing raw request payloads for further handling.

This module constructs HTTP responses by setting status codes, headers, and body content. It operates on the `http_response` type, allowing incremental building of response data. Concrete use cases include assembling HTTP/1.1 responses for web servers, such as setting status 200, adding content-type headers, or attaching JSON payloads.

This module defines types and operations for handling HTTP requests and responses. It provides functions to access request components like method, headers, and body, and to construct responses with status codes, headers, and content. Concrete use cases include building custom HTTP servers that parse incoming requests and generate structured responses for APIs or web services.
